article.headline: Robert Morris 88, Fla. International 61
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Tony Lee scored 21 points and Jimmy Langhurst added 19 on 7-for-7 shooting to lead Robert Morris past Florida International 88-61 on Thursday night. The Colonials (4-2) shot 61 percent from the field and 71 percent from 3-point range. Jeremy Chappell scored 17 points on 6-for-7 shooting for Robert Morris, which outscored FIU 51-36 after halftime -- bolstered by an 8-for-10 performance from 3-point range. Langhurst scored 16 of his points after halftime and he and Chappell combined to shoot 10-for-10 in the final 20 minutes. Kenneth White scored 18 points to lead the Golden Panthers (2-2). Alex Galindo added 13 points and Erick Nsangou scored 11 off the bench. It was Robert Morris' sixth straight road game to open the season.
